rComments: Much better than McKilkenny - she actually goes through problems, asks students questions and gets them involved. Much more of a participative class. Very tough course but she's very smart and knows what she's doing. Always able to explain things to you in a simple and clear way.

Bad teacher..avoid..she expects you to know everything before coming to class..in class she only works examples and mentions the small details..she really seemed to enjoy when students failed..ok marker..you won't learn anything from her..you have to rely on your own for the most part..she makes the class much harder than it really is

Class is WAY too hard for intro to accounting.  I needed a minor in business, not a crazy accounting grind.  Check out the class averages and such.  D's...what does that tell you?  Shes not a bad prof, but you need to come to class. Shes also VERY bureacratic which is really friggin annoying.

With Professor Pyper,expect to rely on reading the book cover to cover to succeed. Her lectures consist mostly of working out examples and not the actual theory. I liked the online exercises because they will give you hints if you get stuck. For the quizzes you have 2 tries, so do it once, practice missed questions and do it again for a good mark.

Doesn't actually teach anything; gives examples of the material being covered, hoping that it will be enough. Basically taught myself from the textbook (MUST BUY FOR SUCCESS). Online quizzes=hassle. WAY too hard for a 60 minute quiz (open book). Take in the summer or with different prof for more guaranteed success.

Loved her. She's always willing to help if you need it. She goes over the homework in class. Even though classes are not mandatory I would suggest to still go because it definitely helps a lot. Great prof, I wish she taught more classes!

Decent prof. Her classes were somewhat helpful. I mostly read the book and learned the stuff on my own. Her midterms and finals are pretty hard, but not impossible to do well on. If you read the book and study you can get an A. If you want a high mark without doing much work, I suggest taking the course in the summer with a different prof.

Was not prepared for final at all!! There were basically no class note, just some stuff scribbled on the board. Midterm and Quizzes are reasonable. Final was HORRIBLE, very long, and difficult for the level being tought. Discouraging for people striving to be an accountant.

WORST prof ever. She didnt go over the last two chaptres which were on the MDterm. She wastes so much time on homework. She does not explain material, she just shows how its done and she assumes that we understand. NEVER TAKE her, take any other prof that lectures ACCT.. Not her!!
Solid Prof, really easy going and approachable, hard quizzes, do the homework
Her course is very demanding. She expects us to know pritty much everything. As a teacher is seems good, and helpful outside of class. It would be more helpfull if she would limit thecourse load.

Had her for both 2340/2341. She explains things pretty clearly at most times, however wastes many lectures on taking up questions. Quizes and midterms can be challenging if you do not prepare yourself for them. In-class notes are not sufficient alone, must use textbook with it!

horrible prof. didnt do midterm review.refused to do a final exam review. refused to take up midterms and quizzes after they were given back!!! ARGHHH HORRIBLE! dont take her class, save urself! take it with someone else in the following semester if u have to

She's an OK prof. The problem with her is that she bases every second lecture on problem solving. If you did not do the homework you're guaranteed to be lost in her course. Very heavy workload and she expects you to do it all... Take her if you like homework and extremely hard quizzes and MTs. It's ultimately your decision...

I found her to be a well organized prof for the most part - but I hated her lectures! And she had no interest in your efforts. I was having a lot of trouble at one point and she just blew me off. You basically pay for a prof that embarrasses you and doesn't care about you as her student.

avoid her as much as you possibly can! she can't explain well since she only scribbles a few things on the board, and her quizzes and MT are tough. she seems like a really nice prof but she does not think about the effort students put into her course
Not helpful, and doesn't give solutions to any quizes or midterms

terrible prof..STAY AWAY FROM HER...she bases your marks on who you are, and make sure to check your exams and quizzes, SHE TOOK MARKS OFF FOR NOTHING, she rips people off for nothing...DO NOT TAKE her, she cant teach, HER QUIZZES ARE EXAMS and EXAMS are like so hardddd, even if you study for like 10hrs straight for a week b4 the exam.
I liked her as much as she is a bit informal with her teachings. Always doing examples therefore it sticks more than just readings..

The class was a lot of work but if you read the text and do the homework you do well.  If you don't like to prepare for class, then  you won't like this class or the prof.  She's nice and has high expectations of students.
No Comments

I had to pay a large amount for the textbook just so that I don't lose out on participation marks because a Wileyplus CD comes with the book. If you don't have the CD you don't get the participation marks. That's bull! I personally don't find the CD even helpful. Her teaching style is very dry. I don't recommend her. You're paying for poor teaching

Basically reviews the homework. That's how she teaches. REFUSED to post solutions for the homework. Quiz = Exam. I spent 5-6 HOURS studying for the first quiz in our class and probably bombed it. Basically in this case you pay tuition to have your homework reviewed briefly. She's nice, but just doesn't seem to get that we're not accountants yet.
